2
00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:02.327
Oh! Hey.

3
00:01:08.268 --> 00:01:10.931
What? I think she
got my wallet. Yeah.

4
00:01:11.104 --> 00:01:12.595
Hey!

5
00:01:13.106 --> 00:01:15.337
Thief. stop! Stop her!

6
00:01:39.866 --> 00:01:40.959
Pss-pss.

7
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:52.445
Oh. come on. Tom.
it wasn't that bad.

8
00:01:52.613 --> 00:01:55.913
Oh. no? Childish drivel.

9
00:01:56.083 --> 00:01:59.212
Well. the acting was fine
and the music was lovely.

10
00:01:59.386 --> 00:02:00.786
What about you. Bruce?

11
00:02:00.954 --> 00:02:04.447
Sorry. Mom. I agree with
Dad. It was kind of lame.

12
00:02:04.625 --> 00:02:06.787
There's no such word as kind of.

13
00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:09.987
- It was totally lame.
- You two are so judgmental.

14
00:02:10.163 --> 00:02:12.689
- What's up. folks?
- Stay calm. Bruce.

15
00:02:13.467 --> 00:02:15.129
Give me your money.

16
00:02:16.336 --> 00:02:17.463
No problem.

17
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:22.132
We're cooperating.

18
00:02:23.510 --> 00:02:25.103
The necklace.

19
00:02:26.613 --> 00:02:28.104
It's okay.

20
00:02:32.319 --> 00:02:33.651
Easy.

21
00:03:05.318 --> 00:03:07.014
Mom? Mom?

22
00:03:08.555 --> 00:03:10.046
Dad? Dad!

23
00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:15.556
Dad.

24
00:03:28.842 --> 00:03:32.244
No!

25
00:03:33.280 --> 00:03:34.407
Sit down.

26
00:03:34.581 --> 00:03:36.709
- Don't move.
- Don't touch my face.

27
00:03:36.883 --> 00:03:39.853
Ease up! MAN 2: Shut up.

28
00:03:40.353 --> 00:03:41.753
I need my pills.

29
00:03:41.922 --> 00:03:45.256
- I need my pills.
- You wish.

30
00:03:45.425 --> 00:03:47.553
Come on. where are my pills?

31
00:03:47.728 --> 00:03:49.560
Back. back. Come on.

32
00:03:51.131 --> 00:03:53.293
Where are my pills?

33
00:03:59.806 --> 00:04:02.503
- Give me my pills. bitch.
- Hold your fire!

34
00:04:04.144 --> 00:04:06.375
Hold your fire! I got this!

35
00:04:08.215 --> 00:04:10.207
Hold your fire.

36
00:04:11.618 --> 00:04:12.711
Easy. easy.

37
00:04:13.653 --> 00:04:17.146
Sir. look at me. Not
at them. look at me.

38
00:04:18.925 --> 00:04:20.791
My name's Jim. Jim Gordon.

39
00:04:20.961 --> 00:04:22.259
What's yours?

40
00:04:23.430 --> 00:04:25.797
I need my pills.

41
00:04:25.966 --> 00:04:27.559
Everything's gonna be all right.

42
00:04:27.734 --> 00:04:29.225
Look at me.

43
00:04:30.237 --> 00:04:31.728
I got your pills right here.

44
00:04:32.639 --> 00:04:34.631
Huh? You want some pills?

45
00:04:35.041 --> 00:04:36.407
Want some pills? All right.

46
00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:40.410
Here you go. here you go. Here
are some pills for you. all right?

47
00:04:44.484 --> 00:04:45.577
These aren't my pills.

48
00:04:54.761 --> 00:04:57.162
Sorry. guys. didn't mean
to bark at you like that.

49
00:04:57.330 --> 00:05:00.198
I got a little bit carried away.
- Get up here.

50
00:05:00.367 --> 00:05:01.699
Hey. come on. Take it easy.

51
00:05:01.868 --> 00:05:03.837
- Come on. hey. guys.
- Hey.

52
00:05:04.938 --> 00:05:06.270
What the hell are you doing?

53
00:05:06.439 --> 00:05:09.034
- We had the drop on him.
- Well. he's dropped. isn't he?

54
00:05:09.209 --> 00:05:11.110
You could have gotten
hurt. Rookie mistake.

55
00:05:11.278 --> 00:05:12.906
Next time. shoot
the son-of-a-bitch.

56
00:05:13.079 --> 00:05:15.014
If I shoot. that
sets everybody off.

57
00:05:15.182 --> 00:05:16.343
Gunfire every which way.

58
00:05:16.516 --> 00:05:19.179
Somebody takes a
cop's gun. you shoot him.

59
00:05:19.352 --> 00:05:21.981
- That's basic. SERGEANT:
Bullock. Gordon. you're up.

60
00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:24.124
Double homicide.
Theater District.

61
00:05:24.291 --> 00:05:26.283
Give me a break.
Shift's nearly over.

62
00:05:26.459 --> 00:05:27.950
Yeah. nearly.

63
00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:41.998
Oh. the legendary Harvey
Bullock. No rest for the wicked. eh?

64
00:05:42.175 --> 00:05:43.507
Tannenbaum. looking crisp.

65
00:05:43.677 --> 00:05:46.044
This is my new partner.
James Gordon. What we got?

66
00:05:46.213 --> 00:05:49.183
Just got here myself.
Male. female. gunshot.

67
00:05:49.349 --> 00:05:51.147
Their kid saw the whole thing.

68
00:05:51.318 --> 00:05:53.116
Poor bastard hasn't
spoke a word yet.

69
00:06:06.867 --> 00:06:08.165
My name's James Gordon.

70
00:06:08.635 --> 00:06:10.365
I'm a detective.

71
00:06:10.537 --> 00:06:11.561
What's your name?

72
00:06:15.242 --> 00:06:17.643
It's okay. You
don't have to talk.

73
00:06:18.545 --> 00:06:21.913
Listen. T. do me a favor.
You didn't see me. okay?

74
00:06:22.082 --> 00:06:25.109
I see you right in front of
me. What's your problem?

75
00:06:25.285 --> 00:06:27.186
That's Thomas and Martha Wayne.

76
00:06:28.521 --> 00:06:31.855
I don't need that hassle. Call Major
Crimes. they'd love to have this.

77
00:06:32.025 --> 00:06:33.755
Yeah. but they're not here.

78
00:06:33.927 --> 00:06:35.987
And your partner's
talking to the witness.

79
00:06:36.162 --> 00:06:40.258
So that makes it your case.

80
00:06:42.302 --> 00:06:43.930
Bruce.

81
00:06:44.871 --> 00:06:47.204
My name is Bruce Wayne.

82
00:06:50.243 --> 00:06:52.735
Can you tell me what
happened. Bruce?

83
00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:11.391
When I was about your
age. a drunk driver hit our car.

84
00:07:12.966 --> 00:07:16.960
Killed my dad. I
was right next to him.

85
00:07:20.073 --> 00:07:22.736
I know how you feel right now.

86
00:07:25.812 --> 00:07:30.944
And I promise you. however dark
and scary the world might be right now...

87
00:07:32.352 --> 00:07:33.945
there will be light.

88
00:07:36.589 --> 00:07:38.717
There will be light. Bruce.

89
00:07:41.261 --> 00:07:43.992
We just got out of the movies.

90
00:07:44.965 --> 00:07:49.164
We were walking through the
alley to catch an uptown cab...

91
00:07:50.670 --> 00:07:52.468
and a man came
out of the shadows.

92
00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:57.468
He was tall with a black mask.

93
00:07:57.644 --> 00:08:00.944
He had a hat and gloves...

94
00:08:01.681 --> 00:08:03.616
and shiny shoes.

95
00:08:03.783 --> 00:08:07.185
He took my dad's wallet
and my mom's necklace.

96
00:08:09.656 --> 00:08:12.319
And then he shot
them for no reason.

97
00:08:14.127 --> 00:08:17.791
I should have done
something. But I was too scared.

98
00:08:17.964 --> 00:08:21.059
There was nothing you could
have done to stop what happened.

99
00:08:21.768 --> 00:08:23.703
But there is something
you can do now.

100
00:08:25.972 --> 00:08:28.203
You can be strong.

101
00:08:29.542 --> 00:08:31.477
Be strong.

102
00:08:33.646 --> 00:08:37.777
I promise you. I will
find the man who did this.

103
00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:44.657
Hey. who the hell is that?

104
00:08:59.839 --> 00:09:00.863
James Gordon.

105
00:09:01.041 --> 00:09:02.942
Alfred Pennyworth.

106
00:09:03.109 --> 00:09:05.374
We're gonna get the
guy that did this. sir.

107
00:09:05.945 --> 00:09:07.709
New boy. are you?

108
00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:09.713
You could say.

109
00:09:11.251 --> 00:09:14.813
Good luck. mate. Come.

110
00:09:16.256 --> 00:09:22.093
Don't look. head up. eyes
front. Don't let them see you cry.

111
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:37.074
Shouldn't we be there
when they move the victims?

112
00:09:37.243 --> 00:09:38.575
Why?

113
00:09:39.546 --> 00:09:41.981
Listen. hotshot. do me a favor.

114
00:09:42.148 --> 00:09:44.447
Don't start talking to
witnesses until I say so.

115
00:09:44.617 --> 00:09:47.951
- What's your problem?
- My problem. soldier boy...

116
00:09:48.121 --> 00:09:51.216
you just caught us a
gigantic flaming ball of crap.

117
00:09:51.391 --> 00:09:53.189
Oh. yeah? How's that?

118
00:09:53.359 --> 00:09:55.624
You never heard of
Thomas and Martha Wayne?

119
00:09:55.795 --> 00:09:57.957
Yeah. sure. The
Wayne Foundation.

120
00:09:58.131 --> 00:10:01.329
Yeah. two of the richest and
most powerful people in Gotham.

121
00:10:01.501 --> 00:10:04.630
You can't even imagine the
pressure if we don't close this quick.

122
00:10:04.804 --> 00:10:06.739
- So let's close it quick.
- Yeah. right.

123
00:10:06.906 --> 00:10:09.068
This is a random
street robbery. Holmes.

124
00:10:09.242 --> 00:10:12.679
Perp could be any one
of 10.000 mopes out there.

125
00:10:14.814 --> 00:10:15.941
Oh. crap.

126
00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:17.209
Order up.

127
00:10:17.383 --> 00:10:20.114
Well. well. well. if it
isn't Montoya and Allen.

128
00:10:20.286 --> 00:10:21.515
Major Crimes Unit.

129
00:10:22.188 --> 00:10:24.953
- This is my new partner. Jim Gordon.
- Nice to meet you.

130
00:10:25.458 --> 00:10:27.791
- Hi. Harvey.
- You're on the Waynes. huh?

131
00:10:27.961 --> 00:10:30.453
- It's a terrible thing.
- Yeah.

132
00:10:30.630 --> 00:10:33.156
- Any leads?
- Just getting started.

133
00:10:33.333 --> 00:10:34.596
I'll be straight.

134
00:10:34.767 --> 00:10:36.895
You want us to take
it off your hands?

135
00:10:38.204 --> 00:10:40.673
- No. no. no.
- Hold on. rook.

136
00:10:40.840 --> 00:10:42.468
Why you want it?

137
00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:43.803
You got a lead?

138
00:10:44.677 --> 00:10:46.669
No. we just need
the press action.

139
00:10:48.214 --> 00:10:49.307
I don't know.

140
00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:51.678
Come on. You know
you're scared of this case.

141
00:10:51.851 --> 00:10:54.013
- I'm scared.
- So do the right thing for once.

142
00:10:54.187 --> 00:10:58.283
For once? Where the hell do
you get the nerve to say that to me?

143
00:10:58.458 --> 00:11:01.155
- You can kiss my ass.
- Okay. you be that way. brother.

144
00:11:01.327 --> 00:11:03.057
We're just trying
to be collegial.

145
00:11:04.998 --> 00:11:09.561
You know. I almost gave it to you.
But you couldn't help yourselves.

146
00:11:09.736 --> 00:11:11.671
You had to go and
be disrespectful.

147
00:11:11.838 --> 00:11:13.397
Okay. Harvey.

148
00:11:13.573 --> 00:11:15.405
Stay frosty.

149
00:11:15.575 --> 00:11:16.736
Good luck.

150
00:11:18.645 --> 00:11:21.205
Self-righteous
do-gooding skell huggers.

151
00:11:22.248 --> 00:11:25.514
Always badmouthing us like
they're such freaking angels. Please.

152
00:11:25.685 --> 00:11:27.916
<i>As mayor of this great city...</i>

153
00:11:28.087 --> 00:11:32.320
<i>I swear to you. the perpetrators of
this heinous crime will be captured...</i>

154
00:11:32.492 --> 00:11:35.985
<i>and will be punished to the
fullest extent. I swear that to you.</i>

155
00:11:36.162 --> 00:11:38.495
Poor bastard. First a
crime wave. and now this.

156
00:11:38.665 --> 00:11:40.691
Take all the people
and resources you need.

157
00:11:40.867 --> 00:11:42.358
Just close this case.

158
00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:44.197
Yes. captain.

159
00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:47.465
Jim. will you give us a minute?

160
00:11:48.741 --> 00:11:50.403
Captain.

161
00:11:54.781 --> 00:11:55.874
The answer is no.

162
00:11:58.284 --> 00:12:00.515
- Teach him the ropes.
- On a weak case?

163
00:12:00.687 --> 00:12:02.849
- Yes.
- Do you want me to change his diapers?

164
00:12:06.793 --> 00:12:10.389
He'll get me killed. I don't care.
I can't go out there with him.

165
00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:22.368
She said you had
to keep me. huh?

166
00:12:22.542 --> 00:12:24.135
Yeah. She did.

167
00:12:24.310 --> 00:12:26.211
She said you're a war hero.

168
00:12:26.379 --> 00:12:29.076
And your daddy was a big-shot
DA back in the olden days.

169
00:12:29.249 --> 00:12:32.242
So I have to keep my
trap shut and do as I'm told.

170
00:12:32.652 --> 00:12:33.711
Ouch.

171
00:12:33.886 --> 00:12:37.914
Listen. kid. You got juice. do
me a favor. ask for a transfer.

172
00:12:38.091 --> 00:12:39.115
Yeah. no.

173
00:12:39.292 --> 00:12:42.262
Sorry. this is where the
action is. You'll get used to me.

174
00:12:42.962 --> 00:12:45.261
Jim. you seem like a nice guy.

175
00:12:45.431 --> 00:12:48.424
But this is not a city
or a job for nice guys.

176
00:12:48.601 --> 00:12:50.069
You understand?

177
00:12:50.403 --> 00:12:52.770
- No.
- And that's your problem.

178
00:12:53.940 --> 00:12:58.469
You're a cynic. A slovenly.
lackadaisical cynic.

179
00:13:01.080 --> 00:13:02.981
You're probably right.

180
00:13:03.549 --> 00:13:06.610
Okay. soldier boy...

181
00:13:06.786 --> 00:13:09.187
let's go roust some muggers.

182
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:12.816
Lackadaisical. Hmm.

183
00:13:22.969 --> 00:13:23.993
Hey.

184
00:13:25.638 --> 00:13:27.004
How you doing?

185
00:13:45.391 --> 00:13:46.689
Guess what this is.

186
00:13:46.859 --> 00:13:49.988
Just tell me. Ed. I want
riddles. I'll read the funny pages.

187
00:13:51.597 --> 00:13:55.557
It's a .45 caliber 300
grain cupronickel wadcutter.

188
00:13:55.735 --> 00:13:57.499
Came out of Thomas
Wayne's chest.

189
00:13:57.670 --> 00:13:59.730
- That's a six dollar bullet.
- Uh-huh.

190
00:13:59.906 --> 00:14:03.206
- What kind of gun...?
- Ah-ah-ah. Don't ask. just tell.

191
00:14:03.743 --> 00:14:07.339
It's from a pistol not known by
our database. No prints either.

192
00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:08.947
What else you got?

193
00:14:09.115 --> 00:14:11.584
What's nowhere but everywhere
except where something is?

194
00:14:11.751 --> 00:14:12.844
Nothing?

195
00:14:14.053 --> 00:14:16.318
You need professional
help. Nygma. Seriously.

196
00:14:16.489 --> 00:14:18.117
Let's go.

197
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:21.225
So I'm thinking. our
man wears shiny shoes...

198
00:14:21.394 --> 00:14:25.490
uses high-end ammo. and nobody
on the street knows who he is?

199
00:14:25.665 --> 00:14:27.156
Maybe he's not from the street.

200
00:14:27.333 --> 00:14:29.700
Like. a debonair playboy
robber does it for kicks?

201
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:31.735
Who would pretend to
be a street robber. huh?

202
00:14:31.904 --> 00:14:35.671
A professional killer. or somebody with
a personal grudge against the Waynes.

203
00:14:35.842 --> 00:14:38.903
How'd this professional know the
Waynes would come down that alley?

204
00:14:39.078 --> 00:14:40.102
Good question.

205
00:14:40.279 --> 00:14:43.772
Essen said we don't catch a break
in the first 48. go see Fish Mooney.

206
00:14:43.950 --> 00:14:47.409
- Fish Mooney? Works for Carmine Falcone?
- Her. Theater district's her turf.

207
00:14:47.587 --> 00:14:49.681
Anything happens
there. she hears about it.

208
00:15:02.402 --> 00:15:04.530
Why didn't we come to her first?

209
00:15:04.704 --> 00:15:07.105
She's kind of a last resort.

210
00:15:12.445 --> 00:15:13.538
Tell Fish I'm here.

211
00:15:16.983 --> 00:15:18.042
Hmm.

212
00:15:18.217 --> 00:15:21.016
Unh! FISH: I still
care for you deeply.

213
00:15:21.187 --> 00:15:23.588
But I don't believe that
you care for me anymore.

214
00:15:23.756 --> 00:15:27.318
I care for you.

215
00:15:27.493 --> 00:15:30.395
Then where's my money?

216
00:15:30.563 --> 00:15:32.429
I'll get it. I'll get it.

217
00:15:36.736 --> 00:15:38.068
Boy.

218
00:15:38.938 --> 00:15:39.418
Sorry.

219
00:15:39.442 --> 00:15:42.340
If you let this hair
go frizzy. you will be.

220
00:15:45.077 --> 00:15:46.739
Ma'am. Detective
Bullock is here.

221
00:15:49.081 --> 00:15:51.812
- Keep him warm.
- Yes. ma'am

222
00:15:54.520 --> 00:15:57.115
Hey. Oswald. you want a turn?

223
00:15:57.657 --> 00:16:00.718
- May I?
- Knock yourself out. kid.

224
00:16:01.160 --> 00:16:03.356
Thank you. Mr. Gilzean.

225
00:16:14.941 --> 00:16:17.274
- Harvey. Ha. ha.
- Fish.

226
00:16:17.743 --> 00:16:21.441
Where have you been?

227
00:16:21.614 --> 00:16:22.877
Where haven't I been?

228
00:16:26.786 --> 00:16:29.654
- Who's the friend?
- Detective James Gordon. ma'am.

229
00:16:29.822 --> 00:16:33.554
Hmm. Well. aren't
you a cool glass of milk.

230
00:16:34.260 --> 00:16:37.094
Ma'am. was that screaming
we heard back there?

231
00:16:37.263 --> 00:16:39.960
Yes. My boys are
watching a scary movie.

232
00:16:40.132 --> 00:16:42.124
- Really.
- No.

233
00:16:42.301 --> 00:16:45.635
Actually. one of my staff has
been stealing money from me.

234
00:16:45.805 --> 00:16:48.297
So we're beating his punk ass.

235
00:16:48.474 --> 00:16:50.705
Relax. junior. Fish
gets some leeway.

236
00:16:50.877 --> 00:16:53.972
Her staff are rough
characters. need firm handling.

237
00:16:54.146 --> 00:16:56.877
So this isn't a
social visit. then.

238
00:16:57.049 --> 00:17:00.679
Unfortunately not. Brass sent me by
to talk to you about the Wayne murders.

239
00:17:00.853 --> 00:17:02.014
Terrible thing.

240
00:17:04.090 --> 00:17:09.051
Junior. if you're worried. go back there
and see if anyone wants to press charges.

241
00:17:09.228 --> 00:17:12.528
- If that's okay with you. Fish.
- Oh. I don't mind at all. Harvey.

242
00:17:30.583 --> 00:17:33.178
- Oswald. whoa.
- Yeah. take it easy. Penguin.

243
00:17:33.352 --> 00:17:35.446
You know I don't
like to be called that.

244
00:17:35.621 --> 00:17:37.112
Ooh. Scary.

245
00:17:37.757 --> 00:17:38.918
How's everybody doing?

246
00:17:39.825 --> 00:17:40.849
Who are you?

247
00:17:41.027 --> 00:17:42.893
James Gordon. G.C.P.D.

248
00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:45.293
Oh. you came with Harvey. huh?

249
00:17:45.464 --> 00:17:47.695
Glad to know you.
James. I'm Butch Gilzean.

250
00:17:49.335 --> 00:17:50.598
Drop the bat.

251
00:17:51.637 --> 00:17:53.230
Oh. come on. now.

252
00:17:53.406 --> 00:17:56.843
Oswald and Raul here were just
having a little fun. weren't you. boys?

253
00:17:57.343 --> 00:18:01.110
- All in fun.
- No problem. Fun.

254
00:18:02.782 --> 00:18:03.943
You're a new guy. huh?

255
00:18:05.351 --> 00:18:07.115
How do you like Gotham so far?

256
00:18:07.286 --> 00:18:09.482
Well enough.

257
00:18:12.058 --> 00:18:13.959
See you around.

258
00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:22.424
Oh. hey.

259
00:18:22.602 --> 00:18:24.867
Everything all right back there?

260
00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:28.639
It's always good
to see you. Harvey.

261
00:18:57.269 --> 00:18:59.135
And look at you and
your excellent suit.

262
00:19:00.172 --> 00:19:04.610
You know. I'm so happy you don't
have to wear that silly uniform anymore.

263
00:19:04.777 --> 00:19:08.544
- You told me it looked good.
- I lied.

264
00:19:10.216 --> 00:19:13.243
- You ready to rock and roll?
- Uh...

265
00:19:13.419 --> 00:19:15.251
Barbara. I'm beat.

266
00:19:15.421 --> 00:19:17.219
Do we really have
to go to this thing?

267
00:19:17.990 --> 00:19:20.858
No. of course not.

268
00:19:21.027 --> 00:19:23.292
- Thank you.
- You owe me.

269
00:19:27.533 --> 00:19:30.298
So talk to me.

270
00:19:30.469 --> 00:19:33.337
We're getting nowhere
on the Wayne case.

271
00:19:34.173 --> 00:19:36.665
I made a promise to Bruce
Wayne. and I can't deliver.

272
00:19:37.443 --> 00:19:38.741
But you will.

273
00:19:39.445 --> 00:19:41.209
I don't know.

274
00:19:41.514 --> 00:19:42.982
Maybe I'm out of my depth.

275
00:19:44.250 --> 00:19:47.709
Hey. I very much doubt
you are out of your depth.

276
00:19:47.887 --> 00:19:52.222
But even if you are. you
know how to swim. don't you?

277
00:19:53.592 --> 00:19:54.890
Yes. I do.

278
00:19:55.695 --> 00:19:56.822
So swim.

279
00:19:58.731 --> 00:20:00.825
I'll swim. You're right.

280
00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:02.400
Are you hungry?

281
00:20:02.568 --> 00:20:05.094
I'm all right. I had a few dogs.

282
00:20:05.271 --> 00:20:08.673
When I'm Mrs. Gordon and
you're living here all the time...

283
00:20:08.841 --> 00:20:12.039
I'm gonna put you on
a proper healthy diet.

284
00:20:12.211 --> 00:20:13.577
Mm-hm.

285
00:20:30.996 --> 00:20:34.592
I've got a lead. Meet me at
Fourth and Grundy in an hour.

286
00:20:34.767 --> 00:20:36.235
On my way.

287
00:20:54.520 --> 00:20:55.954
Hey.

288
00:20:57.323 --> 00:20:58.552
You all right?

289
00:20:58.724 --> 00:21:00.352
Couple drinks. I'll be fine.

290
00:21:00.526 --> 00:21:01.721
Bullock...

291
00:21:02.261 --> 00:21:05.993
Fish Mooney heard from one of her
fences a guy tried to sell him an antique.

292
00:21:06.165 --> 00:21:11.001
Four strand pearl necklace with
gold settings. one strand broken.

293
00:21:11.170 --> 00:21:12.968
- Like Martha Wayne was wearing.
- Mm.

294
00:21:13.439 --> 00:21:16.102
Guy's name is Mario Pepper.

295
00:21:18.144 --> 00:21:23.105
Career street thug. Long sheet for robbery.
assault. rape. extortion. drug dealing.

296
00:21:23.816 --> 00:21:25.614
Nice guy.

297
00:21:31.924 --> 00:21:33.552
Hi.

298
00:21:34.093 --> 00:21:36.187
- What's your name?
- Ivy.

299
00:21:36.362 --> 00:21:38.490
Ivy. is daddy home?

300
00:21:38.664 --> 00:21:40.257
You don't wanna talk to daddy.

301
00:21:40.432 --> 00:21:41.593
Why's that. Ivy?

302
00:21:44.336 --> 00:21:45.395
He's mean.

303
00:21:45.571 --> 00:21:47.631
Hey. who is it?

304
00:21:50.376 --> 00:21:53.141
Mario Pepper. we need to talk.

305
00:21:54.113 --> 00:21:55.604
I've done nothing.

306
00:21:56.148 --> 00:21:58.640
So it'll be a pleasant talk.

307
00:22:00.986 --> 00:22:02.978
Where were you last
Saturday around 9:30?

308
00:22:03.155 --> 00:22:06.319
I was here at home
with my family.

309
00:22:06.492 --> 00:22:08.120
That's right. He was here.

310
00:22:08.594 --> 00:22:10.324
A pearl necklace sound familiar?

311
00:22:11.630 --> 00:22:12.791
No.

312
00:22:12.965 --> 00:22:16.493
Then I guess you don't mind we.
uh. take a look around the place.

313
00:22:17.670 --> 00:22:19.002
You need a warrant.

314
00:22:19.171 --> 00:22:20.867
You're a felon on parole.

315
00:22:21.040 --> 00:22:22.633
All we need is reasonable cause.

316
00:22:40.159 --> 00:22:42.628
Stop! Stop or I'll shoot!

317
00:23:21.767 --> 00:23:22.962
Out of the way!

318
00:24:08.747 --> 00:24:10.215
Thanks.

319
00:24:21.794 --> 00:24:23.592
What kind of guy
wouldn't do that?

320
00:24:26.999 --> 00:24:28.490
Probable? I had to.

321
00:24:44.483 --> 00:24:45.815
We got him.

322
00:24:47.386 --> 00:24:49.150
We got him.

323
00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:27.853
Mario Pepper was framed
by Fish Mooney and the cops.

324
00:25:30.162 --> 00:25:32.222
I saw Ms. Mooney with
Martha Wayne's necklace.

325
00:25:32.831 --> 00:25:37.360
She was discussing how to get it into
Pepper's home. inside a bag of drugs.

326
00:25:37.536 --> 00:25:40.216
This was shortly after she met
with Detectives Bullock and Gordon...

327
00:25:40.372 --> 00:25:42.170
from the homicide squad.

328
00:25:42.341 --> 00:25:44.833
Mooney works with
Carmine Falcone's mob.

329
00:25:45.010 --> 00:25:47.502
You saying Falcone
had the Waynes killed?

330
00:25:47.679 --> 00:25:50.877
- I'm just telling you what I saw.
- Why snitch on your own boss?

331
00:25:51.050 --> 00:25:55.215
I confess. that poor orphan
boy pricked my conscience.

332
00:25:55.387 --> 00:25:56.855
No.

333
00:25:57.022 --> 00:25:59.082
You wanna push Fish out. huh?

334
00:26:02.094 --> 00:26:05.826
That's beside the point.
I've done my civic duty.

335
00:26:06.965 --> 00:26:08.092
Good day to you both.

336
00:26:56.415 --> 00:26:58.646
You kept your promise.

337
00:26:59.118 --> 00:27:00.313
Thank you.

338
00:27:01.386 --> 00:27:03.184
I'm sorry you
didn't see a trial.

339
00:27:04.423 --> 00:27:05.447
That's okay.

340
00:27:23.442 --> 00:27:25.968
Renee. long time.

341
00:27:27.045 --> 00:27:28.104
Yeah.

342
00:27:32.651 --> 00:27:36.281
Sorry to drop by
unexpected like this.

343
00:27:37.956 --> 00:27:39.219
How have you been?

344
00:27:40.359 --> 00:27:42.021
I'm good.

345
00:27:42.194 --> 00:27:44.754
- You?
- All good.

346
00:27:44.930 --> 00:27:47.058
You're running an
art gallery now. right?

347
00:27:47.232 --> 00:27:50.031
- Yeah.
- That's so cool.

348
00:27:50.936 --> 00:27:52.165
And I'm engaged.

349
00:27:52.938 --> 00:27:53.997
Yeah.

350
00:27:54.806 --> 00:27:55.933
James Gordon. huh?

351
00:27:57.543 --> 00:28:00.411
- That's why I'm here.
- Oh?

352
00:28:00.579 --> 00:28:03.447
The G.C.P.D. framed Mario
Pepper for the murder of the Waynes.

353
00:28:04.883 --> 00:28:07.876
- What?
- They framed and killed an innocent man.

354
00:28:08.053 --> 00:28:10.784
And you're here to tell me
that James was in on this?

355
00:28:10.956 --> 00:28:12.549
- Yes.
- And what's your proof?

356
00:28:12.724 --> 00:28:15.057
I can't tell you.
but it's the truth.

357
00:28:15.227 --> 00:28:17.992
James Gordon is not a good guy.

358
00:28:18.163 --> 00:28:19.256
You deserve better.

359
00:28:19.898 --> 00:28:23.300
James Gordon is the most
honest man I've ever met.

360
00:28:23.468 --> 00:28:25.232
He's not capable of doing that.

361
00:28:25.404 --> 00:28:28.499
- You sure you know what he's capable of?
- Yes. I know him.

362
00:28:28.674 --> 00:28:30.006
Does he know you?

363
00:28:30.609 --> 00:28:31.668
Don't.

364
00:28:32.978 --> 00:28:34.913
Like I know you?

365
00:28:42.387 --> 00:28:44.356
Here you are.

366
00:28:47.426 --> 00:28:51.022
Barbara. what's wrong?

367
00:28:52.297 --> 00:28:53.856
Did you frame Mario Pepper?

368
00:28:58.036 --> 00:29:00.369
- No.
- I knew it.

369
00:29:00.539 --> 00:29:03.031
- Who told you?
- Doesn't matter. as long as it's not true.

370
00:29:03.208 --> 00:29:06.406
- It's not. Who told you it was?
- Nobody.

371
00:29:07.512 --> 00:29:09.208
Bee. I know when you're lying.

372
00:29:11.416 --> 00:29:13.214
Montoya.

373
00:29:17.556 --> 00:29:19.267
What's your evidence
that Pepper was framed?

374
00:29:19.291 --> 00:29:21.658
I was wrong to reveal
that information to Barbara.

375
00:29:21.827 --> 00:29:24.763
- We're old friends.
- I asked what evidence you have.

376
00:29:24.930 --> 00:29:29.265
You'll see the evidence when we get you
and your crooked friends into a courtroom.

377
00:29:29.434 --> 00:29:30.766
We're working on it.

378
00:29:32.170 --> 00:29:33.502
Save your energy.

379
00:29:33.672 --> 00:29:36.073
If Pepper was
framed. I'll find out.

380
00:29:36.241 --> 00:29:38.676
Hey. you got a
problem here. Gordon?

381
00:29:38.844 --> 00:29:43.145
And then you and you just
need to stay out of my way.

382
00:29:47.052 --> 00:29:48.680
Mrs. Pepper - Go away.

383
00:29:48.854 --> 00:29:52.655
Ma'am. if your husband was
innocent. you need to talk to me.

384
00:29:59.564 --> 00:30:03.160
If your husband didn't kill the Waynes.
how'd he come to have the necklace?

385
00:30:03.335 --> 00:30:05.531
You bastards planted it on him?

386
00:30:05.704 --> 00:30:07.070
Bastards.

387
00:30:08.473 --> 00:30:11.341
Alice. how would the
police have the necklace?

388
00:30:11.510 --> 00:30:13.775
We didn't kill the Waynes.
- So you say.

389
00:30:13.945 --> 00:30:17.473
God knows my husband had his
demons. but he never killed nobody.

390
00:30:19.318 --> 00:30:21.344
Can I see his shoes?

391
00:30:21.853 --> 00:30:22.946
Shoes?

392
00:30:29.728 --> 00:30:33.130
- This is all of them?
- Uh-huh.

393
00:30:34.866 --> 00:30:36.300
Damn.

394
00:30:36.468 --> 00:30:39.734
Framed? How you
figure? You were there.

395
00:30:39.905 --> 00:30:40.964
We framed him?

396
00:30:41.139 --> 00:30:43.665
Somebody could've planted
the necklace on Pepper.

397
00:30:43.842 --> 00:30:46.334
- Mooney could've set the whole thing up.
- Why?

398
00:30:46.511 --> 00:30:48.946
To cover up for the real killer.

399
00:30:49.114 --> 00:30:50.673
Mooney works for Falcone.

400
00:30:51.683 --> 00:30:53.549
Maybe Falcone wanted
the Waynes killed.

401
00:30:53.719 --> 00:30:55.551
Wait. wait. wait.

402
00:30:55.854 --> 00:30:58.517
Why would such a nutty
idea even enter your head?

403
00:30:59.491 --> 00:31:01.551
Montoya from MCU.

404
00:31:01.727 --> 00:31:04.595
That pill-head looney-bird?
What's her proof?

405
00:31:04.763 --> 00:31:08.165
- Wouldn't tell me. Didn't trust me.
- She doesn't have any.

406
00:31:08.333 --> 00:31:09.858
If they did. they'd
have used it.

407
00:31:10.569 --> 00:31:13.164
Pepper didn't wear shiny shoes.

408
00:31:13.572 --> 00:31:15.200
He didn't own any shiny shoes.

409
00:31:15.374 --> 00:31:17.605
Shiny shoes. Mother of God.

410
00:31:17.776 --> 00:31:22.009
Shiny shoes. Just suppose for a
moment. just suppose Pepper was innocent.

411
00:31:22.180 --> 00:31:23.546
I killed him.

412
00:31:23.715 --> 00:31:26.446
- We killed him.
- We killed him.

413
00:31:27.552 --> 00:31:30.181
We'd lose our jobs
at the very least.

414
00:31:30.355 --> 00:31:33.291
The case is closed.
Forget about it.

415
00:31:36.194 --> 00:31:38.824
Even if the real killers
are still out there?

416
00:31:38.848 --> 00:31:39.848
Yes.

417
00:31:40.165 --> 00:31:42.964
This is very perilous
stuff you're messing with.

418
00:31:43.602 --> 00:31:45.730
Listen to me for once. Jim.

419
00:31:45.904 --> 00:31:47.304
Forget about it.

420
00:31:58.383 --> 00:31:59.874
Detective Gordon.

421
00:32:00.619 --> 00:32:01.814
Tell Mooney I'm here.

422
00:32:02.821 --> 00:32:06.019
- Regarding what. shall I say?
- Mario Pepper.

423
00:32:06.191 --> 00:32:07.921
Mario...

424
00:32:08.093 --> 00:32:10.460
- May I ask why?
- No.

425
00:32:10.629 --> 00:32:12.928
No. Yes. Heh.

426
00:32:13.098 --> 00:32:14.122
None of my business.

427
00:32:15.967 --> 00:32:19.301
James Gordon. How nice.

428
00:32:19.471 --> 00:32:22.532
The day I met you. when I was
out back there with your boys...

429
00:32:22.707 --> 00:32:24.801
what did you and
Harvey talk about?

430
00:32:25.811 --> 00:32:27.905
Shouldn't you ask Harvey?

431
00:32:28.079 --> 00:32:29.570
He's your partner.

432
00:32:29.748 --> 00:32:32.013
- I'm afraid he might lie.
- Hmm.

433
00:32:32.651 --> 00:32:35.485
He might. And you
think I'll tell you the truth?

434
00:32:39.424 --> 00:32:40.448
You just did.

435
00:32:43.228 --> 00:32:44.526
James. wait.

436
00:32:51.236 --> 00:32:53.228
You have a little
danger in your eye.

437
00:32:55.340 --> 00:32:57.775
I wonder what you
plan to do with that.

438
00:32:57.943 --> 00:32:59.639
You'll have to wait and see.

439
00:33:01.279 --> 00:33:02.872
I hate surprises.

440
00:33:17.562 --> 00:33:19.622
Detective Bullock?

441
00:33:21.266 --> 00:33:22.290
Miss Kean.

442
00:33:22.467 --> 00:33:26.165
Um. James went for a walk last
night. and he never came back.

443
00:33:26.338 --> 00:33:28.898
Have you heard from him?
I'm really worried about him.

444
00:33:29.908 --> 00:33:31.399
He's on a stake-out.

445
00:33:32.143 --> 00:33:34.874
Yeah. his phone probably
ran out of juice. is all.

446
00:33:35.046 --> 00:33:36.480
Oh.

447
00:33:37.482 --> 00:33:39.383
Right. well. that's a relief.

448
00:33:39.551 --> 00:33:41.281
- Thank you.
- No problem.

449
00:34:05.076 --> 00:34:08.740
Wait. wait. wait.

450
00:34:11.049 --> 00:34:12.847
Shut up.

451
00:34:16.721 --> 00:34:17.961
Hey. what are you doing?

452
00:34:18.356 --> 00:34:20.518
Over here. you'll get a better angle.
- What?

453
00:34:20.692 --> 00:34:24.629
- You're a director now?
- Don't get fresh. I'm just saying.

454
00:34:26.565 --> 00:34:28.363
Hey. Butch.

455
00:34:29.834 --> 00:34:31.325
Harvey.

456
00:34:31.603 --> 00:34:33.071
Who told you we'd be here?

457
00:34:33.238 --> 00:34:36.640
Everybody knows this is
where you take your problems.

458
00:34:37.976 --> 00:34:40.946
- That's my partner you got there.
- Ex-partner.

459
00:34:41.479 --> 00:34:42.913
Oh.

460
00:34:43.748 --> 00:34:44.841
Let me talk to Fish.

461
00:34:46.551 --> 00:34:49.680
I'm not afraid of death
so much as I am of dying.

462
00:34:49.854 --> 00:34:53.484
I. um. wanna die how my father
died. peacefully. in his sleep.

463
00:34:53.658 --> 00:34:56.560
Not like his screaming.
terrified. passengers.

464
00:35:03.001 --> 00:35:05.766
- Yeah? BUTCH: Bullock
showed up at the plant.

465
00:35:05.937 --> 00:35:09.635
- Wants to talk to you.
- Put him on. Give me a moment. kid.

466
00:35:09.808 --> 00:35:11.504
You're doing good.

467
00:35:12.310 --> 00:35:14.006
<i>- Fish?</i>
- Speaking.

468
00:35:14.179 --> 00:35:15.613
Don't be like that.

469
00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:17.408
Listen. you gotta let my boy go.

470
00:35:17.582 --> 00:35:21.451
<i>- How long we been friends?</i>
- For a long time. Until today.

471
00:35:21.620 --> 00:35:23.646
I did a big favor for
you and your pals...

472
00:35:23.822 --> 00:35:27.520
and now it's gonna blow up in my
face on account of your stupidity.

473
00:35:27.692 --> 00:35:29.024
The kid's not your problem.

474
00:35:29.194 --> 00:35:33.529
He was hipped to the frame by Major
Crimes. they'll be coming after you.

475
00:35:33.898 --> 00:35:37.096
- How did they get onto me?
- The usual way. I guess.

476
00:35:37.268 --> 00:35:38.531
Somebody talked.

477
00:35:38.703 --> 00:35:40.535
<i>Huh. Not one of my people.</i>

478
00:35:40.705 --> 00:35:42.970
That's what everybody says.

479
00:35:45.644 --> 00:35:48.808
- True.
- Listen. you gotta let my boy go. Hmm?

480
00:35:48.980 --> 00:35:51.381
You kill my partner. I
gotta come after you.

481
00:35:53.485 --> 00:35:55.386
<i>I don't wanna do it. but
how am I gonna look...</i>

482
00:35:55.553 --> 00:35:57.545
you kill my partner. I
don't make a move?

483
00:35:57.722 --> 00:35:59.452
All right.

484
00:35:59.624 --> 00:36:02.253
But promise me that you'll
keep him under control.

485
00:36:02.427 --> 00:36:04.055
- I promise.
<i>- Cool.</i>

486
00:36:04.496 --> 00:36:05.987
Put Butch on. please.

487
00:36:10.435 --> 00:36:11.459
Yeah. boss.

488
00:36:11.636 --> 00:36:15.164
That son-of-a-bitch just threatened
me. You hang him up with his partner.

489
00:36:15.640 --> 00:36:17.336
You got it.

490
00:36:17.809 --> 00:36:18.902
Hey. how you doing?

491
00:36:19.077 --> 00:36:21.069
I'm good. We're going home.

492
00:36:21.246 --> 00:36:21.578
Yeah?

493
00:36:21.602 --> 00:36:23.841
I'm just glad everything
could work out...

494
00:36:26.184 --> 00:36:27.208
Cops.

495
00:36:30.221 --> 00:36:32.087
Bless your heart.

496
00:36:32.257 --> 00:36:35.318
Would you be a sweet
boy and rub my feet?

497
00:36:40.665 --> 00:36:43.100
Give me a moment. darling.
I haven't forgotten you.

498
00:36:43.268 --> 00:36:44.861
I like you. You're funny.

499
00:36:48.239 --> 00:36:51.437
Now. this amateur
nonsense is a good sign.

500
00:36:51.609 --> 00:36:53.441
There used to be
some discipline.

501
00:36:53.611 --> 00:36:56.843
Falcone is getting old and soft.

502
00:36:57.015 --> 00:36:58.415
It's time.

503
00:36:58.583 --> 00:37:01.212
Somebody has to take
over. it might as well be me.

504
00:37:01.386 --> 00:37:02.911
Yes. it might as well.

505
00:37:03.088 --> 00:37:07.253
And you? You're like a son
to me. You know that. Oswald?

506
00:37:07.425 --> 00:37:09.223
I feel that way also.

507
00:37:09.394 --> 00:37:11.829
Which is what I
don't understand.

508
00:37:11.996 --> 00:37:14.090
After all I've done for you...

509
00:37:14.265 --> 00:37:18.862
and right when I'm on the verge
of great things. you betray me?

510
00:37:19.037 --> 00:37:21.199
Why would you
betray your mother?

511
00:37:21.372 --> 00:37:23.603
I don't know what you mean.

512
00:37:23.775 --> 00:37:26.040
It was you.

513
00:37:27.245 --> 00:37:29.714
You snitched to the MCU.

514
00:37:30.515 --> 00:37:32.381
You wanna know how I know?

515
00:37:33.017 --> 00:37:37.455
Because only you saw me
with the pearls. no one else.

516
00:37:41.726 --> 00:37:43.160
It was Gilzean.

517
00:37:43.328 --> 00:37:44.660
He's the snitch.

518
00:37:47.232 --> 00:37:48.598
No.

519
00:37:48.767 --> 00:37:51.965
- Gilzean is loyal.
- So am I.

520
00:37:52.137 --> 00:37:55.130
I would open a vein right here
and now if you asked me to.

521
00:38:00.044 --> 00:38:01.910
Go on. then.

522
00:38:02.080 --> 00:38:03.742
Open one.

523
00:38:06.484 --> 00:38:09.545
I. uh... I was
speaking poetically.

524
00:38:11.289 --> 00:38:12.587
Prove it.

525
00:38:13.124 --> 00:38:17.653
Prove your loyalty.
my little Penguin.

526
00:38:19.264 --> 00:38:23.065
Please. Miss
Mooney. Please. don't.

527
00:38:28.106 --> 00:38:32.009
You broke my heart!

528
00:38:38.716 --> 00:38:40.446
Are we rolling?

529
00:38:40.618 --> 00:38:42.484
How you doing?

530
00:38:43.454 --> 00:38:44.649
Been better.

531
00:38:44.823 --> 00:38:47.122
Thanks for trying to help.

532
00:38:47.525 --> 00:38:48.993
Wish I hadn't.

533
00:38:49.394 --> 00:38:51.727
- Did you just slap my hand?
- Hey. Butch!

534
00:38:51.896 --> 00:38:52.955
Save your breath.

535
00:38:53.498 --> 00:38:56.957
If it was up to me. you'd get a bullet
in the head and a decent funeral.

536
00:38:57.635 --> 00:38:58.967
But Fish has her ways.

537
00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:03.904
Yo. Franky! Showtime.

538
00:39:33.771 --> 00:39:35.069
Don Falcone.

539
00:39:35.240 --> 00:39:38.699
Forgive me. young man. I
forget what your name is.

540
00:39:38.877 --> 00:39:40.402
Or perhaps I never knew it.

541
00:39:41.045 --> 00:39:42.843
Gilzean. sir.

542
00:39:43.014 --> 00:39:44.243
Gilzean.

543
00:39:44.415 --> 00:39:47.214
Tell Miss Mooney
she's too impetuous.

544
00:39:47.385 --> 00:39:51.345
If she wants to kill policemen.
she has to ask permission.

545
00:39:52.257 --> 00:39:53.520
Yes. sir.

546
00:39:58.196 --> 00:39:59.892
There are rules.

547
00:40:03.034 --> 00:40:04.627
Cut them down.

548
00:40:04.802 --> 00:40:06.964
That's right. there are rules.

549
00:40:10.675 --> 00:40:13.702
It's good to meet
you at last. James.

550
00:40:14.279 --> 00:40:17.010
I knew your father very well.

551
00:40:17.181 --> 00:40:20.083
The best DA this city ever had.

552
00:40:20.251 --> 00:40:22.811
He and I understood each other.

553
00:40:22.987 --> 00:40:25.889
There was respect.
Friendship. even.

554
00:40:26.424 --> 00:40:27.483
Friendship?

555
00:40:29.627 --> 00:40:33.723
Trust me. that's the only
reason you're alive now.

556
00:40:34.432 --> 00:40:38.665
Blood doesn't lie. I know that when
you leave here. you'll do the right thing.

557
00:40:38.836 --> 00:40:40.395
I will.

558
00:40:40.571 --> 00:40:41.766
I'll tell what I know.

559
00:40:41.940 --> 00:40:43.738
Which is what?

560
00:40:43.908 --> 00:40:47.675
I know that you own the police
department. probably the mayor too.

561
00:40:47.845 --> 00:40:50.041
And I was sure that you
had the Waynes killed.

562
00:40:50.214 --> 00:40:53.412
But if you did. you wouldn't
risk letting me live. would you?

563
00:40:54.419 --> 00:40:58.982
Then again. how did Fish Mooney
come to have Martha Wayne's necklace?

564
00:40:59.157 --> 00:41:01.786
- A replica?
- Yes.

565
00:41:01.960 --> 00:41:05.021
But if you didn't have them
killed. why frame Mario Pepper?

566
00:41:06.731 --> 00:41:08.791
Or are you covering
up for somebody else?

567
00:41:08.967 --> 00:41:11.459
Who knows who killed the Waynes.

568
00:41:11.636 --> 00:41:12.934
Some lowlife.

569
00:41:13.104 --> 00:41:15.266
We needed a culprit
before the funeral.

570
00:41:15.440 --> 00:41:20.310
Pepper was sacrificed so that the people
of Gotham would see swift justice done.

571
00:41:20.478 --> 00:41:22.970
So they can feel
safe and secure.

572
00:41:23.147 --> 00:41:25.582
- And that matters so much to you.
- Of course.

573
00:41:25.750 --> 00:41:27.616
I'm a businessman.

574
00:41:27.785 --> 00:41:31.847
You can't have organized
crime without law and order.

575
00:41:33.524 --> 00:41:37.586
I love this city. and
I see it going to hell.

576
00:41:37.762 --> 00:41:40.459
But I won't let it fall
apart without a fight.

577
00:41:40.631 --> 00:41:43.499
You make a life of
crime sound very noble.

578
00:41:44.068 --> 00:41:46.867
You have a hard head.
James. just like your father.

579
00:41:47.038 --> 00:41:50.031
Don't be self-righteous.
Don't be arrogant.

580
00:41:50.208 --> 00:41:52.040
You want me to keep
quiet about all this.

581
00:41:52.210 --> 00:41:54.679
Gotham is on a knife edge.

582
00:41:54.846 --> 00:41:58.806
What do you suppose bringing down
city hall and the police force will do?

583
00:41:58.983 --> 00:42:00.042
Even if you could.

584
00:42:01.219 --> 00:42:02.847
Would it make things better?

585
00:42:25.810 --> 00:42:27.676
- Lookit. Jim.
- I'm listening.

586
00:42:27.845 --> 00:42:30.371
I wasn't being honest with you.

587
00:42:31.015 --> 00:42:32.745
But you weren't
ready for the truth.

588
00:42:32.917 --> 00:42:35.216
You didn't tell me because
you were ashamed.

589
00:42:40.058 --> 00:42:41.526
Why are we stopping here?

590
00:42:43.928 --> 00:42:45.692
No. please.
Please. I beg of you.

591
00:42:45.863 --> 00:42:47.195
Shut up!

592
00:42:48.533 --> 00:42:51.196
This is the fool that snitched
to Montoya and Allen.

593
00:42:51.369 --> 00:42:56.535
Falcone wants you to walk him to the end
of that pier and put a bullet in his head.

594
00:42:56.707 --> 00:42:58.733
Then everybody knows
you're with the program.

595
00:43:03.648 --> 00:43:05.207
And if I don't?

596
00:43:05.383 --> 00:43:08.581
Then I'm supposed to
take you out and him too.

597
00:43:10.088 --> 00:43:11.818
Here's the thing.
Jim. I like you.

598
00:43:11.989 --> 00:43:15.448
I might not have the
stomach to do it. but I'll try.

599
00:43:15.626 --> 00:43:19.222
Because if I don't. someone
will get to you quick enough.

600
00:43:19.397 --> 00:43:22.060
Then they're gonna get to
me. probably Barbara as well.

601
00:43:22.233 --> 00:43:23.826
Who knows what you told her.

602
00:43:24.001 --> 00:43:26.994
- I told her nothing.
- You think Falcone cares?

603
00:43:27.638 --> 00:43:30.506
- Come on. you've killed people before.
- That was war!

604
00:43:30.675 --> 00:43:33.577
This is war! We're at war
with scumbags like him.

605
00:43:33.744 --> 00:43:36.509
Sometimes in a war. you gotta
do a bad thing to do good. right?

606
00:43:37.014 --> 00:43:42.282
So. do you do this bad thing. or
do you die and maybe your girl dies?

607
00:43:42.453 --> 00:43:46.982
I might be lackadaisical.
hmm? But that's not a tough call.

608
00:44:01.973 --> 00:44:02.997
Walk.

609
00:44:21.025 --> 00:44:24.189
Please. Mr. Gordon.
just let me live.

610
00:44:24.362 --> 00:44:27.127
I'll do whatever you say.
I'll be your slave for life.

611
00:44:27.298 --> 00:44:32.066
Listen to me. there's a
war coming. a terrible war.

612
00:44:32.236 --> 00:44:35.035
Falcone is losing his grip.
and his rivals are hungry.

613
00:44:35.206 --> 00:44:38.973
There will be chaos. rivers of
blood in the streets. I know it.

614
00:44:39.143 --> 00:44:42.011
I can see it coming.

615
00:44:42.180 --> 00:44:43.808
I'm clever that way.

616
00:44:43.981 --> 00:44:45.142
And I can help you.

617
00:44:45.316 --> 00:44:48.809
- I can be a spy...
- Shut up!

618
00:44:50.655 --> 00:44:52.487
Turn around.

619
00:44:56.727 --> 00:44:58.355
For God's sake. have mercy.

620
00:45:01.766 --> 00:45:04.361
Don't ever come back to Gotham.

621
00:45:18.883 --> 00:45:20.374
Attaboy.

622
00:45:27.925 --> 00:45:29.518
Oh. my God. James.

623
00:45:30.061 --> 00:45:32.030
I've been so worried.

624
00:45:34.765 --> 00:45:36.757
What happened to you?

625
00:46:17.575 --> 00:46:21.979
Hey! Master Bruce! Get
your bloody ass down off there!

626
00:46:22.146 --> 00:46:23.739
How many times have I told you?

627
00:46:31.155 --> 00:46:33.056
Why were you up on the roof?

628
00:46:33.824 --> 00:46:35.759
I'm learning to conquer fear.

629
00:46:36.627 --> 00:46:38.289
Fear doesn't need conquering.

630
00:46:39.263 --> 00:46:42.631
Fear tells you where the
edge is. Fear is a good thing.

631
00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:45.167
And you think I haven't
told him that. do you?

632
00:46:46.137 --> 00:46:49.574
You came here for a reason. I imagine.
- Yes.

633
00:46:50.007 --> 00:46:52.442
Mario Pepper didn't
kill your parents.

634
00:46:53.277 --> 00:46:58.181
He was framed by the police
department and the mob working together.

635
00:46:59.283 --> 00:47:01.115
We killed an innocent man.

636
00:47:02.219 --> 00:47:03.517
Right.

637
00:47:03.688 --> 00:47:06.351
So who did it. then?

638
00:47:06.524 --> 00:47:08.652
I don't know. ALFRED: I see.

639
00:47:08.826 --> 00:47:10.818
Well. sterling work
there. then. mate.

640
00:47:10.995 --> 00:47:14.022
Yes. I'm sorry.

641
00:47:16.667 --> 00:47:18.192
Don't be.

642
00:47:19.670 --> 00:47:22.333
I'm glad he's still alive.

643
00:47:26.043 --> 00:47:27.375
I wanna see him again.

644
00:47:27.912 --> 00:47:33.215
Bruce. I'm asking you to
give me a second chance.

645
00:47:33.984 --> 00:47:36.544
I'm going to find out who
killed your parents and why.

646
00:47:36.721 --> 00:47:40.021
And I'm gonna clean up the
damn police department if I can.

647
00:47:40.691 --> 00:47:42.717
But I can only do
that from the inside.

648
00:47:43.894 --> 00:47:49.856
So I'm asking you to stay
silent about what I've told you.

649
00:47:52.069 --> 00:47:53.697
Your call.

650
00:47:53.871 --> 00:47:56.272
Right. well. that's sort
of convenient. isn't it?

651
00:47:56.440 --> 00:47:57.601
Alfred!

652
00:48:18.529 --> 00:48:19.963
Thank you.

652
00:48:20.305 --> 00:49:20.387
